{# ── SUMMARY · real H2 carrying the urgent-bookkeeping TL;DR prose (baseline tldr body, enriched). (H2: What New York urgent bookkeeping actually is.) ── #}
<section class="section section--compact" id="ny-svc-urgent-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What New York urgent bookkeeping actually is.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="stack-8">
      {%- for p in summary %}<p class="prose">{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SCENARIOS · the real NY deadline triggers (grid-3 buyer-cards). REAL specificity, not a mad-lib. ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-urgent-scenarios">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">When the clock is real</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">The deadlines that send New York businesses here.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Urgent bookkeeping is defined by the clock, not the work. These are the deadline scenarios where current, reconciled books suddenly have to exist &mdash; fast. How fast depends on scope and how complete your records are.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in scenarios %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ s.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── AI SUMMARY · five-question block. (H2: New York urgent bookkeeping, in five questions.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-urgent-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">New York urgent bookkeeping, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <dl class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="ny-svc-urgent-ai-summary-list">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <dt class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</dt>
        <dd class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></dd>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </dl>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── PROCESS · the scoped sprint (grid-3 buyer-cards). 5 frozen H3s VERBATIM. (H2: How urgent bookkeeping works when the clock is running. + 5 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-urgent-process">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">How it works</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">How urgent bookkeeping works when the clock is running.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">A scoped sprint: diagnostic first, prioritized catch-up against the deadline second, reconciled financials third, then a clean handoff. Speed comes from focused scope and a daily cadence &mdash; not from cutting corners.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for p in process %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <p class="buyer-card__opener">{{ p.num }}</p>
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ p.title | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ p.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── SCOPE SPLIT · honest do / won't-pretend (grid-2 buyer-cards). 2 frozen H3s VERBATIM. (H2: What we can do under deadline — and what we won't pretend to. + 2 H3s) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-urgent-scope">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Honest scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What we can do under deadline &mdash; and what we won&rsquo;t pretend to.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The honest line matters most when a deadline is involved. Here is exactly what a TechBrot urgent engagement covers &mdash; and what stays with your CPA or EA.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for col in scopeSplit %}
      <article class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__heading">{{ col.heading | safe }}</h3>
        <ul class="checks-list">
          {%- for li in col.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── WHAT MAKES IT FAST · focused scope + daily cadence + NY sales-tax-ready (checks-list). ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-urgent-fast">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Where the speed comes from</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What makes an urgent engagement fast &mdash; honestly.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Speed under a deadline is a function of scope and records, not heroics. These are the levers that compress the timeline &mdash; and the honest limits on each.</p>
    </header>
    <ul class="checks-list">
      {%- for f in fast %}<li>{{ f | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── ADVISORY · standing brand line (frozen H2 verbatim). (H2: Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-urgent-advisory">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The advisory line</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Automation handles the data entry. We handle the judgment.</h2>
    </header>
    <p class="prose">{{ advisoryBody | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── FAQ · 7 verbatim contract Q/A; visible faq__list = FAQPage schema (same array). (H2: What people ask when they're up against a deadline.) ── #}
<section class="section" id="ny-svc-urgent-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Urgent bookkeeping questions</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What people ask when they&rsquo;re up against a deadline.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="ny-svc-urgent-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="ny-svc-urgent-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# ── EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name (byline-block + trust-row + meta-reviewed). (H2: Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.) ── #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="ny-svc-urgent-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the TechBrot Certified ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="byline-block">
      <div class="byline-block__mark" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline-block__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline-block__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot handles New York urgent bookkeeping engagements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm. Urgent engagements are scoped fast-turnaround catch-up/cleanup against a hard deadline &mdash; including <a href="/find-an-accountant/new-york/sales-tax-help/">NYC/NY sales-tax tie-out</a> where a notice or filing is the driver. TechBrot delivers the books and coordinates with your CPA or EA, who files; it does not file New York taxes or represent clients before any tax authority.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-07</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-07</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-07 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>
